title: David Rock Feinstein Discography [ mp3@320 ] - CAPTAiN_24
description:
=====================================================================================


        === David 'Rock' Feinstein Discography [ mp3@320 ] - CAPTAiN_24 ===


=====================================================================================

David Feinstein is the cousin of Ronnie James Dio and played with him in "Elf",

later to become "Rainbow", and then band leader for heavy metal greats, "The Rods".


David "Rock" Feinstein started early, he picked up the trumpet at 7 years and later 

drums. 18 years old he was in a band called The Cindells that played a mix of folk 

and covers of Cream, Rolling Stones and Beatles - even releasing a few singles. The 

band did however split in 1967, and his cousin, Ronnie Dio asked if Dave (who at the 

time barely played the guitar) could replace the guitarist in Ronnie Dio and the 

Prophets. He accepted, and later handled the strings in Electric Elves, Elves and 

Elf.
